---
/**
 * /service-testing/fleets-v2 — sandbox for the Fleets v2 redesign.
 *
 * Render path: Layout (with `headerVariant="v4"`) → HeaderV4 (the
 * Lefter sidebar) + this page's body. Layout already pads the body
 * with `padding-left: var(--lefter-width)` so we don't have to
 * hand-offset the hero around the sidebar.
 *
 * NOT yet wired through the ServicePageV2 template — this is a
 * scratch surface to iterate the design before formalizing into
 * the template. Below the hero, the body still carries the
 * pre-existing AI-slop sections from /solutions/fleets — those
 * will be gutted next.
 *
 * SCROLL BEHAVIOR — intentionally FREE-SCROLLING for now.
 * No scroll-snap, no pinned sections, no parallax, no scroll-
 * tied animations on this page. Once the section list is
 * finalized, the next iteration will introduce a "section
 * flowing motion" pattern (likely scroll-snap on a vertical
 * track, or pinned-with-progress segments). Don't add scroll-
 * controlling CSS or JS here until the content structure is
 * stable.
 */
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Fleet Charging Solutions — Evium Charging"
  description="Turnkey EV fleet charging infrastructure. Depot design, load management, phased rollout, and 24/7 monitoring — engineered for fleets that can't afford downtime."
  headerVariant="v4"
  bodyClass="page-fleets-v2"
>

  {/* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       HERO — Round 5: centered cinematic premium
       ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
       Pattern: Apple / Tesla / Stripe-style centered hero.
       Different in shape from every prior round (all of which
       were left- or bottom-anchored).

         · Cinematic full-bleed photo with a soft 4-edge
           atmospheric vignette + a focused radial darken
           behind the centered type. No chrome pills, no
           floating elements, no competing visual blocks.
         · Optically centered content (~46% from top — slight
           upward bias from dead center, where the eye
           naturally lands). Photo breathes top + bottom.
         · Editorial type composition:
             eyebrow (small dash-bookended caps)
             headline (parallel two-statement: "Always
                       charged. / Always running.")
             green hairline accent
             subhead (one focused sentence)
             primary CTA (premium gradient green pill)
             text link (magazine-style "Or see what we
                       build for fleets")
         · Buttons: gradient pill with subtle vertical sheen,
           multi-layer shadow stack (inset highlight + dark
           bottom edge + green outer halo + dark drop shadow),
           hover lift+scale. Secondary is an animated-
           underline magazine link in caps.
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}
  <section class="fv2-hero" aria-label="Fleet Charging — Evium">

    {/* Photo — full saturation, full bleed. Updated to the
        Evium-branded depot rendering (chargers carry the
        Evium wordmark instead of OEM branding). */}
    <picture class="fv2-hero-photo" aria-hidden="true">
      <img
        src="/images/heroes/fleet-depot-hero-evium.png"
        alt=""
        loading="eager"
        fetchpriority="high"
        draggable="false"
      />
    </picture>

    {/* Veil — left-anchored darken so the typography zone
        on the LEFT half stays legible while the right half
        of the photo (chargers, vans, sky) plays at full
        saturation. Plus subtle top + bottom cinematic edge
        fade for the framed-photo feel. */}
    <div class="fv2-hero-veil" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    {/* Top-left content block — eyebrow + headline + subhead.
        Sits above the row of vans in the photo's middle band. */}
    <div class="fv2-hero-content">
      <p class="fv2-hero-eyebrow">
        <span class="fv2-hero-eyebrow-dash" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span>For Fleets That Don't Stop</span>
      </p>

      <h1 class="fv2-hero-title">
        <span class="fv2-hero-title-line">We run the chargers.</span>
        <span class="fv2-hero-title-line fv2-hero-title-line--accent">You run the fleet.</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="fv2-hero-sub">
        Evium handles every step of your EV depot transition &mdash;
        design, install, monitor, maintain &mdash; so going electric
        actually cuts both your operating costs and your emissions.
      </p>
    </div>

    {/* Bottom-left action block — primary CTA + magazine link.
        Sits BELOW the vans, over the photo's asphalt band so
        the depot scene plays uncovered between the text above
        and the buttons below. */}
    <div class="fv2-hero-actions">
      <!-- href targets #final-cta so the page smooth-scrolls
           to the closing CTA band instead of jumping cross-
           page. The smooth-scroll handler below intercepts the
           click for an animated transition. -->
      <a class="fv2-cta-primary" href="#final-cta" data-fv2-scroll>
        <span class="fv2-cta-primary-face" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="fv2-cta-primary-inner">
          <span>Talk to a fleet specialist</span>
          <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </span>
      </a>

      <a class="fv2-link" href="#fleet-strategy">
        <span>Or see what we build</span>
        <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    /* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       FLEETS-V2 — HERO (Round 5: centered cinematic premium)
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */

    .fv2-hero {
      position: relative;
      min-height: 100vh;
      width: 100%;
      overflow: hidden;
      background: #0a1822;
      isolation: isolate;
      /* Block layout — content + actions are both absolutely
         positioned to occupy the upper-left and lower-left
         zones respectively, leaving the photo's middle band
         (warehouse + vans + chargers) UNCOVERED. */
      --fv2-skew: -14deg;
      /* Single source of truth for the left-edge inset of
         both content blocks, so they line up vertically. */
      --fv2-edge: clamp(56px, 7vw, 110px);
    }

    /* ── Photo ──────────────────────────────────────────────
       Slight grading lift only — saturation 1.08 + contrast
       1.05 to compensate for the cinematic veil over it. */
    .fv2-hero-photo {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      z-index: 0;
    }
    .fv2-hero-photo img {
      width: 100%;
      height: 100%;
      object-fit: cover;
      object-position: 60% 42%;
      filter: saturate(1.08) contrast(1.05);
      user-select: none;
    }

    /* ── Veil — TWO-ZONE darken ─────────────────────────────
       Content lives in the upper-left, actions live in the
       lower-left, the depot photo plays UNCOVERED in between.
       So the veil has two focused darken zones (one for each
       content block) plus subtle top + bottom edge fades.
       The middle band (~30%-70% vertical) — where the vans
       and chargers live — stays fully transparent. */
    .fv2-hero-veil {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      z-index: 1;
      pointer-events: none;
      background:
        /* Upper-left text-zone darken */
        radial-gradient(
          ellipse 55% 38% at 22% 18%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.88) 0%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.62) 26%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.30) 52%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.08) 78%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0)    100%
        ),
        /* Lower CTA-zone darken — centered ~50% horizontal
           and slightly lower (90% vs 86%) to follow the CTAs
           to their new bottom-right position. Stays clear of
           the road arrow on the left and the curb on the
           right; photo plays at full saturation on both. */
        radial-gradient(
          ellipse 38% 26% at 48% 90%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.78) 0%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.5)  28%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.22) 56%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.05) 80%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0)    100%
        ),
        /* Top + bottom edge fades — bridges the page chrome
           above and the next section below without a hard
           rectangle of darken. */
        linear-gradient(
          to bottom,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.40) 0%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.05) 14%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0)    32%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0)    68%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.10) 86%,
          rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.40) 100%
        );
    }

    /* ── Left-anchored content ──────────────────────────────
       Vertically centered, LEFT-aligned in the left ~50%
       of the viewport. Generous padding from the lefter
       sidebar's edge gives premium breathing room. */
    /* ── Top-left content block (eyebrow + headline + sub) ── */
    .fv2-hero-content {
      position: absolute;
      top: clamp(60px, 7vh, 100px);
      left: var(--fv2-edge);
      right: clamp(40px, 5vw, 80px);
      max-width: 920px;
      z-index: 4;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }

    /* ── Eyebrow ────────────────────────────────────────────
       Single dash on the LEFT only (left-aligned content),
       attention-grabbing copy. */
    .fv2-hero-eyebrow {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 14px;
      margin: 0 0 clamp(22px, 2.2vw, 32px);
      font-family: 'Maven Pro', sans-serif;
      font-size: clamp(0.66rem, 0.78vw, 0.78rem);
      font-weight: 900;
      letter-spacing: 0.32em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: #2DC856;
      text-shadow:
        0 1px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.75),
        0 0 22px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
    }
    .fv2-hero-eyebrow-dash {
      width: clamp(32px, 3.4vw, 50px);
      height: 1.5px;
      background: linear-gradient(to right, #2DC856, rgba(45, 200, 86, 0));
      border-radius: 1px;
    }

    /* ── Headline ───────────────────────────────────────────
       Two parallel statements: "We run the chargers." (white)
       / "You run the fleet." (green accent). Same size,
       same weight — color carries the contrast. */
    .fv2-hero-title {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: 'Maven Pro', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 900;
      line-height: 1.0;
      letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      color: #ffffff;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: clamp(4px, 0.5vw, 10px);
      /* No max-width — let lines wrap only if container shrinks */
    }
    .fv2-hero-title-line {
      font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 4.6vw, 4.6rem);
      white-space: nowrap;
      text-shadow:
        0 6px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.78),
        0 2px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.55);
    }
    .fv2-hero-title-line--accent {
      color: #2DC856;
      text-shadow:
        0 6px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.72),
        0 0 50px rgba(45, 200, 86, 0.28);
    }

    /* ── Subhead ────────────────────────────────────────────
       Editorial treatment: a green vertical hairline rule
       on the left edge anchors it to a typographic column
       (magazine-style), and a multi-layer text-shadow gives
       it real lift off the photo behind. The rule ALSO
       gives the subhead a clear visual identity separate
       from the headline above. */
    .fv2-hero-sub {
      position: relative;
      margin: clamp(22px, 2.2vw, 32px) 0 0;
      padding: clamp(4px, 0.4vw, 8px) 0 clamp(4px, 0.4vw, 8px) clamp(16px, 1.6vw, 22px);
      font-family: 'Maven Pro', sans-serif;
      font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.16vw, 1.16rem);
      line-height: 1.55;
      letter-spacing: 0.005em;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.92);
      max-width: 48ch;
      text-wrap: pretty;
      /* Multi-layer shadow — first a tight dark halo for
         crisp legibility, then a softer wider one for
         depth against the photo. */
      text-shadow:
        0 1px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.85),
        0 2px 18px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.55),
        0 0 28px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
    }
    /* Green vertical hairline on the LEFT edge — fades from
       transparent at top to bright green in the middle and
       back to transparent at the bottom, so it reads as a
       deliberate editorial column-mark, not a hard rule. */
    .fv2-hero-sub::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      top: 4%;
      bottom: 4%;
      left: 0;
      width: 2px;
      background: linear-gradient(
        to bottom,
        rgba(45, 200, 86, 0)    0%,
        rgba(45, 200, 86, 0.55) 18%,
        rgba(45, 200, 86, 0.7)  50%,
        rgba(45, 200, 86, 0.55) 82%,
        rgba(45, 200, 86, 0)    100%
      );
      border-radius: 1px;
    }

    /* ── Bottom action block ────────────────────────────────
       Positioned with breathing room on BOTH sides:
         · Left edge sits past the directional arrow on the
           asphalt (which spans roughly 15-30% from viewport
           left), with a clear gap.
         · Right edge stops well short of the curb / parking-
           platform transition (which begins around ~60% from
           viewport left), so the button doesn't touch the
           sidewalk. */
    .fv2-hero-actions {
      position: absolute;
      bottom: clamp(40px, 5vh, 80px);
      /* Pushed slightly further right (was 39vw, now 41vw)
         to balance the bigger button size below. */
      left: clamp(380px, 41vw, 590px);
      z-index: 4;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: clamp(16px, 1.6vw, 22px);
    }

    /* ── Primary CTA — brand-skewed parallelogram ───────────
       NOT a generic pill. The button SHAPE is skewed at the
       same -14° angle as Evium's nav battery dividers, then
       the inner content is counter-skewed back to upright so
       the text reads horizontally inside a slanted shape.
       Result: an industrial, brand-cohesive button shape that
       can't be mistaken for a generic pill.

       Construction:
         · The <a> element is the skewed parallelogram.
         · A `.face` ::before sub-layer paints the green
           gradient + multi-layer shadows, also skewed.
         · The inner span counter-skews the text +14° so the
           type reads upright while the shape stays slanted. */
    .fv2-cta-primary {
      position: relative;
      display: inline-flex;
      padding: 0;
      background: transparent;
      border: 0;
      text-decoration: none;
      cursor: pointer;
      -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;
      isolation: isolate;
      transition: transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(.22, 1, .36, 1);
    }
    /* Skewed face — the visible green parallelogram. Sits
       behind the inner content, paints the gradient + shadows. */
    .fv2-cta-primary-face {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      z-index: -1;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #3bd866 0%, #2DC856 50%, #25b04d 100%);
      transform: skewX(var(--fv2-skew));
      border-radius: 4px;
      box-shadow:
        inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65),
        inset 0 -1px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.22),
        inset 1px 0 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.10),
        inset -1px 0 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.10),
        0 22px 50px rgba(45, 200, 86, 0.45),
        0 8px 22px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
      transition:
        background 0.32s ease,
        box-shadow 0.4s cubic-bezier(.22, 1, .36, 1),
        transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(.22, 1, .36, 1);
    }
    /* Inner content — counter-skewed so text reads upright.
       Slightly larger size: bumped padding + font so the
       button has more visual presence on the photo. */
    .fv2-cta-primary-inner {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 16px;
      padding: clamp(19px, 1.95vw, 25px) clamp(38px, 4vw, 56px);
      color: #0a1822;
      font-family: 'Maven Pro', sans-serif;
      font-size: clamp(0.82rem, 0.98vw, 0.98rem);
      font-weight: 900;
      letter-spacing: 0.2em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      transition: gap 0.32s cubic-bezier(.22, 1, .36, 1);
    }
    .fv2-cta-primary-inner svg {
      width: 17px;
      height: 17px;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      transition: transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(.22, 1, .36, 1);
    }

    .fv2-cta-primary:hover,
    .fv2-cta-primary:focus-visible {
      transform: translateY(-3px);
      outline: none;
    }
    .fv2-cta-primary:hover .fv2-cta-primary-face,
    .fv2-cta-primary:focus-visible .fv2-cta-primary-face {
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #4ae07a 0%, #38d562 50%, #2DC856 100%);
      box-shadow:
        inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.82),
        inset 0 -1px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.22),
        inset 1px 0 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.14),
        inset -1px 0 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.10),
        0 30px 64px rgba(45, 200, 86, 0.6),
        0 12px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.55);
    }
    .fv2-cta-primary:hover .fv2-cta-primary-inner,
    .fv2-cta-primary:focus-visible .fv2-cta-primary-inner {
      gap: 18px;
    }
    .fv2-cta-primary:hover svg,
    .fv2-cta-primary:focus-visible svg {
      transform: translateX(4px);
    }
    .fv2-cta-primary:active {
      transform: translateY(-1px);
    }

    /* ── Secondary text link — magazine style ───────────────
       Sits below the primary CTA. Animated underline scales
       from 55% → 100% on hover; arrow slides; color shifts
       to green. NO box, NO outline — integrates with the
       photo's atmosphere via type alone. */
    .fv2-link {
      position: relative;
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 11px;
      padding: 4px 2px;
      font-family: 'Maven Pro', sans-serif;
      font-size: clamp(0.74rem, 0.86vw, 0.86rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.2em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.82);
      text-decoration: none;
      text-shadow: 0 1px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
      cursor: pointer;
      -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;
      transition: color 0.22s ease, gap 0.32s cubic-bezier(.22, 1, .36, 1);
    }
    .fv2-link span {
      position: relative;
      display: inline-block;
    }
    .fv2-link span::after {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      right: 0;
      bottom: -2px;
      height: 1px;
      background: currentColor;
      transform-origin: center;
      transform: scaleX(0.55);
      opacity: 0.6;
      transition:
        transform 0.42s cubic-bezier(.22, 1, .36, 1),
        opacity 0.22s ease,
        background 0.22s ease;
    }
    .fv2-link svg {
      width: 13px;
      height: 13px;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      transition: transform 0.32s cubic-bezier(.22, 1, .36, 1);
    }
    .fv2-link:hover,
    .fv2-link:focus-visible {
      color: #2DC856;
      gap: 14px;
      outline: none;
    }
    .fv2-link:hover span::after,
    .fv2-link:focus-visible span::after {
      transform: scaleX(1);
      opacity: 1;
      background: #2DC856;
    }
    .fv2-link:hover svg,
    .fv2-link:focus-visible svg {
      transform: translateX(4px);
    }

    /* ── Responsive ─────────────────────────────────────── */
    @media (max-width: 759px) {
      /* On mobile the dual-block layout collapses: text and
         CTAs both anchor to the TOP-left as a single stacked
         column. The narrow viewport means there's no room
         for the photo's middle band to play uncovered between
         them anyway, so a unified darken serves better. */
      .fv2-hero-photo img { object-position: 70% 40%; }
      .fv2-hero-title-line { white-space: normal; }
      .fv2-hero-veil {
        background:
          linear-gradient(
            to right,
            rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.92) 0%,
            rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.78) 38%,
            rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.48) 72%,
            rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.28) 100%
          ),
          linear-gradient(
            to bottom,
            rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.45) 0%,
            rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.05) 16%,
            rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.05) 78%,
            rgba(6, 18, 26, 0.55) 100%
          );
      }
      .fv2-hero-content {
        position: relative;
        top: auto;
        right: auto;
        left: auto;
        max-width: 100%;
        padding: clamp(60px, 9vh, 100px) 20px 0 24px;
      }
      .fv2-hero-actions {
        position: relative;
        bottom: auto;
        left: auto;
        padding: clamp(28px, 4vw, 40px) 24px clamp(48px, 7vh, 80px) 24px;
      }
      .fv2-cta-primary { width: auto; }
      .fv2-hero-sub { max-width: 100%; }
    }
  </style>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       VALUE-PROP BRIDGE  (NEW — sourced from OG replica)
       Lighter sage-on-cream register that breaks up the dark-
       teal section run and gives skimmers a 30-second exit
       ramp before the deeper pain-points / strategy / hardware
       blocks. Two pieces:
         1. ICP italic line — names the target customer in one
            breath so visitors self-qualify in seconds.
         2. 3-up benefit cards (Capacity / Cost / Future-Proofing)
            — at-a-glance value prop adopted from the OG layout.
  ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="fv2-bridge" aria-labelledby="fv2-bridge-icp">
    <div class="fv2-bridge-inner">

      <header class="fv2-bridge-head">
        <p class="fv2-bridge-eyebrow">
          <span class="fv2-bridge-eyebrow-rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span>For Fleet Operators</span>
          <span class="fv2-bridge-eyebrow-rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        </p>
        <p id="fv2-bridge-icp" class="fv2-bridge-icp">
          Built for logistics operators, last-mile delivery, regional
          transport, and warehouses optimizing operations and
          <em>reducing their emissions.</em>
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="fv2-bridge-grid">

        <!-- Card 1 — Capacity. Box-truck silhouette etched into
             the lower-right corner as an editorial watermark. -->
        <article class="fv2-bridge-card" data-fv2-card="capacity">
          <svg class="fv2-bridge-card-mark" viewBox="0 0 64 48" aria-hidden="true">
            <rect x="3" y="10" width="34" height="24" rx="2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linejoin="round" />
            <path d="M37 16h11l8 8v10h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
            <path d="M43 34h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" />
            <circle cx="14" cy="38" r="4.2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" />
            <circle cx="46" cy="38" r="4.2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" />
          </svg>
          <div class="fv2-bridge-card-body-wrap">
            <h3 class="fv2-bridge-card-title">Capacity for Large Fleets</h3>
            <p class="fv2-bridge-card-body">
              Our infrastructure is engineered to support extensive
              fleets, ensuring that every vehicle is ready when it's
              needed without creating bottlenecks at the depot or
              limiting daily routes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Card 2 — Cost-Effective. Bold $ in a circle —
             unambiguous "money/cost" symbol that reads at any
             size as a watermark. -->
        <article class="fv2-bridge-card" data-fv2-card="cost">
          <svg class="fv2-bridge-card-mark" viewBox="0 0 64 64" aria-hidden="true">
            <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="28" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" />
